message.content:
cs.NI, cs.MA, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper discusses a mobile ad hoc network based on Wi-Fi Direct technology. 
- cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) is also likely as the paper describes a routing layer that enables communication between devices in a group and multi-hop communication across a group. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is another possible category as the paper discusses a distributed network of mobile devices. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper describes the development of a routing layer to support communication between devices. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses the implementation of a system on a group of mobile devices.
